  "prompt": "Are there truly a large percentage of narcissists whom use drugs addictively?",
  "response": "The relationship between narcissism and substance use disorder is complex and not fully understood. Some research suggests that individuals with narcissistic traits may be more prone to substance abuse issues due to factors such as impulsivity, a desire for self-enhancement, and difficulty with emotional regulation. \n\nNarcissists may use drugs as a way to cope with underlying insecurities, enhance their self-image, or manage stress. However, not all individuals with narcissistic traits will develop substance use disorders, and not all substance users exhibit narcissistic traits.\n\nIt's also important to note that addiction can affect people from a variety of psychological backgrounds, and while there may be a correlation between narcissism and addiction, it does not imply that a significant percentage of narcissists will use drugs addictively. More research is needed to determine the exact prevalence and nature of this relationship. If you're looking for specific statistics or studies, I recommend consulting psychological journals or articles that focus on addiction and personality disorders.",
